  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001403.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) Šarrukin , king of the world , was victorious in 34 battles . He demolished all city walls as far as the shore of the sea . He moored the ships of Meluhha , Magan , and Dilmun at the quay of Agade ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001403.14",
      "line_range": "14",
      "translation": "(14) In Tuttul , Šarrukin , the king , prostrated himself before Dagan and prayed to him . ( Dagan then ) gave him the Upper land , ( including ) Mari , Yarmuti , and Ebla , as far as the cedar forests and the mountains of precious metal ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001403.29",
      "line_range": "29",
      "translation": "(29) In the presence of Šarrukin , the king whom Enlil made a man without opponent , 13 ( units ) of troops eat daily ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001403.38",
      "line_range": "38",
      "translation": "(38) Whoever obliterates this inscription , may An obliterate his name , may Enlil put an end to his lineage , may Inana cut his ... short !"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001403.49",
      "line_range": "49",
      "translation": "(colophon 1, 1) The inscription on its socle ."
    }
  ],
